# Design Elements Commonality

Design standards for consistent UI/UX. Apply intelligently when creating new UI components.

## Icons

**Rule**: Use lucide-react icons instead of emoji icons.

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
import { Info, Edit2, Trash2, Plus } from 'lucide-react'
<Info className="h-4 w-4" />

// ❌ WRONG
<p>ℹ️ Information text</p>
```

## Button Colors

**Rule**: Selection buttons (teams, weekdays, slots) use blue. Action buttons (Save, Cancel, Add, Delete) use semantic variants.

```tsx
// ✅ Selection buttons (blue)
<Button className={cn(
  isSelected ? 'bg-blue-600 text-white' : 'bg-gray-100 text-gray-700'
)}>
  {team}
</Button>

// ✅ Action buttons (semantic)
<Button type="submit">Save</Button>
<Button variant="outline" onClick={onCancel}>Cancel</Button>
<Button variant="destructive" onClick={handleDelete}>Delete</Button>
```

## Dropdown Menus (Select)

**Rule**: Use shared `Select` components (Radix) in dialogs/forms. Avoid native `<select>`.

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
import { Select, SelectContent, SelectItem, SelectTrigger, SelectValue } from '@/components/ui/select'

<Select value={staffId} onValueChange={setStaffId}>
  <SelectTrigger>
    <SelectValue placeholder="Select SPT" />
  </SelectTrigger>
  <SelectContent>
    {staff.map((s) => (
      <SelectItem key={s.id} value={s.id}>{s.name}</SelectItem>
    ))}
  </SelectContent>
</Select>

// ❌ WRONG - native select in dialogs
<select value={staffId} onChange={(e) => setStaffId(e.target.value)}>
  <option value="">Select SPT</option>
</select>
```

## Dialog Width

**Rule**: Default to `max-w-lg` (512px). Allow text wrapping. Only use wider dialogs for tables/large forms.

```tsx
// ✅ Default (most dialogs)
<DialogContent className="max-w-lg">
  <p className="text-xs text-muted-foreground">
    Instruction text that wraps naturally
  </p>
</DialogContent>

// ✅ Wide (only for tables/large forms)
<DialogContent className="max-w-2xl max-h-[90vh] overflow-y-auto">
  {/* Wide content */}
</DialogContent>

// ❌ WRONG - unnecessarily wide
<DialogContent className="max-w-4xl">
  <p>Short text</p>
</DialogContent>
```

## Tooltip Background

**Rule**: Tooltip background should be white.

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
<div className="px-2 py-1 text-xs bg-white border border-border rounded-md shadow-md">
  {tooltipContent}
</div>
```

## Summary Checklist

When creating new UI components:
- [ ] Icons use lucide-react (not emojis)
- [ ] Selection buttons use blue (`bg-blue-600 text-white` when selected)
- [ ] Dropdowns use `Select` components (not native `<select>`) in dialogs/forms
- [ ] Action buttons use semantic variants (Save/Cancel/Add/Delete)
- [ ] Dialog width matches content (default `max-w-lg`, allow text wrapping)
- [ ] Tooltips use white background
